1
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,640
You two keep an eye on her.

2
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,039
I'll find someone to ask.

3
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:50,800
Brother Long.

4
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,400
I owe you 45,000, right?

5
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,720
Do I get 5,000 back?

6
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,000
Forget it, keep it.

7
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,810
Are you asking me for money?

8
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,800
Take it.

9
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:11,080
Leaving the door open in broad daylight isn't a good idea, is it?

10
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,080
Who are you?

11
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,200
Who am I?

12
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,160
Why are you looking at me?

13
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:16,640
Get him.

14
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,480
He looks like a cop.

15
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,360
I can read.

16
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:27,560
This watch,

17
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,280
what's going on with it?

18
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:29,940
Whose is it?

19
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,720
This watch is mine.

20
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,720
Whose is it really?

21
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,520
Mine, Officer.

22
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:36,600
Yours?

23
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,720
Okay, then come with me.

24
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,480
This watch is linked to a criminal case.

25
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,810
We need to investigate.

26
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:43,200
Officer,

27
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,520
this watch isn't mine.

28
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:46,840
Not yours?

29
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,640
It's not mine.

30
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,120
Hers.

31
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,280
Zhao Lu.

32
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,079
I know.

33
00:02:56,079 --> 00:02:57,810
This watch isn't yours either.

34
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,960
Come with us.

35
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,280
Let's have a chat at the station.

36
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,120
Hurry, Lu.

37
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,570
Go with the officer.

38
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:04,960
Get your shoes.

39
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,840
Go with the officer.

40
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:07,920
Just say you don't want the money

41
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,480
anymore.

42
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,440
You people.

43
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,490
Take care, officer.

44
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,930
Tell me, how did you get this watch?

45
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,640
I stole it.

46
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,680
I didn't want to.

47
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,640
But I owe people money.

48
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,890
You saw it today.

49
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,000
Guys like Long.

50
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:34,010
If you came a step later, I would've...

51
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:36,920
Besides.

52
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:40,280
The guest in 208,

53
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,960
he just left the watch on the nightstand.

54
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,250
He didn't keep an eye on it himself.

55
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,680
I just borrowed it for an emergency.

56
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,520
And then?

57
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,650
How did you steal it?

58
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,000
In his room,

59
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,200
isn't there a dumbwaiter?

60
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,820
I slipped it out through the dumbwaiter.

61
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,800
I swear,

62
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:20,959
it's my first time doing this.

63
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,060
My hands are trembling from fear.

64
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,440
I didn't think the watch was worth much.

65
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:28,400
Later, I found out it's worth 50,000.

66
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,720
I was thinking that after things quieted down,

67
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:32,080
I would sell the watch.

68
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,840
I didn't expect

69
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,640
that he would find out.

70
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,720
You can't just kill him to silence him

71
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,580
because he found out you stole it.

72
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,240
What are you talking about, silencing him?

73
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,920
Silence who?

74
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,960
No, I killed someone?

75
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,159
You're acting, right?

76
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,400
What acting?

77
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,600
No, who died?

78
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,960
Li Ting died.

79
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,560
He died in Room 208.

80
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,520
He died?

81
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,360
How could he be dead?

82
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,480
Officers,

83
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,760
if you say I stole, I admit it.

84
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,560
But I wouldn't dare kill anyone.

85
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,740
I try to avoid him as much as possible.

86
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,960
Avoid him?

87
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:18,560
Why did you want to avoid him?

88
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,320
How could I not?

89
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,080
He bothered me every day.

90
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,080
That day, I was cleaning his room

91
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,580
and ran into him again.

92
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:30,700
What are you doing?

93
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,159
You again.

94
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:35,090
Didn't I say I don't need cleaning?

95
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,640
Done.

96
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:40,100
Are you trying to steal something again?

97
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,360
What kind of person are you?

98
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,440
Don't touch my suitcase.

99
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:45,880
Okay.

100
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,159
I am warning you for the last time.

101
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:50,200
Do not touch my things without my permission.

102
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,530
Don't move. Don't move.

103
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,640
Where is my watch?

104
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,920
You won't let this watch thing go, will you?

105
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,240
Didn't you already search me?

106
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,560
I didn't take it.

107
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,040
Still won't admit it, huh?

108
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:07,480
Do you really think I don't know how you stole my watch?

109
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,080
I know how you took it.

110
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,840
Do you want me to call the police right now?

111
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,880
Don't call the police. Don't.

112
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,540
Please don't call the police.

113
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,920
I took it.

114
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,020
I'll go home and get it for you.

115
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,120
It's fine if you don't want to return it.

116
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,540
How about keeping me company for a night?

117
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,320
Do you think your looks are worth my watch?

118
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,250
Go get the watch.

119
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,640
Take the mop away.

120
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,760
Dumbwaiter.

121
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,920
Is this the reason you quit on May 13th?

122
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,600
Yes.

123
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,480
I couldn't work there anymore.

124
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,440
Couldn't work?

125
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,960
I now have every reason to suspect you.

126
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:23,280
Because Li Ting said you stole,

127
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,120
you sought personal revenge

128
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,720
and killed him to silence him.

129
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,880
No, officer.

130
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,720
You need evidence to back up your words.

131
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,400
There are security cameras at the door.

132
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,120
How could I have gone in and out?

133
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,450
Didn't you just say there's a dumbwaiter?

134
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,880
A dumbwaiter?

135
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,560
That's for sending food, okay?

136
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,600
Someone my size would get stuck in it.

137
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,930
Have you ever been in it?

138
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,920
How do you know you'd get stuck?

139
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,090
Why don't you try it?

140
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,840
See if you get stuck.

141
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,760
Unless it's a kid.

142
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,640
Ma'am.

143
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:09,520
The dumbwaiter's capacity is 35 kilograms.

144
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,580
Doesn't that clear Zhao Lu of suspicion?

145
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,880
Did we all get it wrong?

146
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,760
Isn't this just an accident?

147
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,360
He just fell to his death?

148
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:22,680
No.

149
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:26,420
Zhuang Lan's and my analysis can't be wrong.

150
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,320
There must have been a second person at the scene.

151
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,440
Cheng Mo is right.

152
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,169
Captain Zhuang.

153
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,120
The autopsy report is out.

154
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,799
At the exact same spot on the back of the victim's head,

155
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,840
there are indeed signs of a second impact.

156
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,840
A second impact?

157
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,440
Yes.

158
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,960
That explains

159
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,559
why the victim's hands

160
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,640
were in such a strange position.

161
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,560
He didn't die immediately after falling.

162
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:52,720
Instead, someone grabbed his head

163
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:55,580
and smashed it hard against the edge of the bathtub.

164
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,280
So.

165
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,000
That's why there are such strange handprints.

166
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:04,160
Then how did that person get in?

167
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,640
The only ways I can think of are the main door

168
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,720
and the dumbwaiter.

169
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:12,160
But the dumbwaiter can only hold 35 kilograms.

170
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,920
How could a normal person fit in it?

171
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,720
Could it be a minor

172
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,680
or a dwarf?

173
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,440
That's not right either.

174
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,160
There are traces of cleaning in the dumbwaiter.

175
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,560
But I still found

176
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,880
a newly left partial fingerprint.

177
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,340
Judging from the outline,

178
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:27,840
it belongs to an adult.

179
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,890
Then who could it be?

180
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,520
In Li Ting's social connections,

181
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:35,450
there is absolutely no one who fits the description.

182
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,620
There is such a person.

183
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:43,280
This person is someone close to Li Ting.

184
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,840
So when he was in the room,

185
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,480
Li Ting could take a shower without any reservations.

186
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,640
Zhuang Lan and I analyzed the scene.

187
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,560
From the gap left in the curtains,

188
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:54,290
we suspect Li Ting had been watching this person.

189
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:57,600
And this person might be the killer we're looking for.

190
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,240
One person is highly suspicious.

191
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:02,570
Li Ting even went to see her before he died.

192
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,120
That is his wife,

193
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:04,800
Lu Chen.

194
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,440
Can't the 513 case be closed yet?

195
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,440
Mainly because we haven't figured out

196
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,880
his MO yet.

197
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,800
Let me tell you.

198
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,520
Keeping the Accident Investigation Team running

199
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,440
has put me under a lot of pressure.

200
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:39,720
Three days.

201
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,920
I'll give you three more days.

202
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,800
I must see the final report.

203
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:46,720
Okay.

204
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,720
How is Cheng Mo doing?

205
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,960
His ability to handle cases is quite good.

206
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,240
But sometimes he acts like a child.

207
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,730
If you find him troublesome...

208
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,480
No need.

209
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,860
I'm already used to babysitting.

210
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,560
Go ahead.

211
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,800
Ms. Lu, here's the situation.

212
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:33,930
It has been confirmed that your husband died in an accident.

213
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,610
You still need to sign here.

214
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:53,920
Alright.

215
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:54,960
That's all.

216
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,220
The paperwork is done.

217
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,480
Ms. Lu.

218
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,880
My condolences.

219
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,640
Honey.

220
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,400
I'm taking you home now.

221
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,960
Officer Fang, Mr. Cheng.

222
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,040
Thank you for your hard work.

223
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,680
The paperwork is done.

224
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,880
I'll be leaving now.

225
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,450
My condolences.

226
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:24,970
My condolences.

227
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,920
I really don't understand.

228
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,000
She is clearly a major suspect.

229
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,660
Why did we let her go so easily?

230
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,860
Where is the evidence?

231
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,760
Take a look at this first.

232
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,760
She has an alibi.

233
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,320
It's too deliberate.

234
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,440
The weather wasn't hot,

235
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,500
but she wore so much

236
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:03,210
and intentionally walked under the only camera in the village.

237
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,040
Yeah.

238
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:06,000
But you need evidence.

239
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,200
According to Mr. Shao's estimation,

240
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,640
the time of death was 8:00 PM.

241
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,360
She has a solid alibi, okay?

242
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,200
We need evidence.

243
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:16,680
Sometimes,

244
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:20,640
taking a step back is the best way forward.
